               <p>JOHN BOARDS. I am a <rs id="t18281023-175-viclabel1026" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-175-victim935 t18281023-175-viclabel1026"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18281023-175-crimeloc1027">Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-175-crimeloc1027" type="placeName" value="Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-175-crimeloc1027" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-175-off1024 t18281023-175-crimeloc1027"></join>. On the 8th of October I had information given me; I went to my door, and a neighbour cried, "Up the court:" I went up the court, and met the prisoner, with these trousers under his arm, which had been hanging at my door-post; I collared and took him into my shop - the trousers were safe ten minutes before.</p>
               <p>
            
